SIMPLE: scavenge
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scavenge
<hw>Scav"enge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cleanse, as
streets, from filth.</def> <rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to salvage (usable items or material) from discarded
or waste material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To remove (burned gases) from the cylinder after a
working stroke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scavenge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scavenge
<hw>Scav"enge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<fld>(Internal-combustion Engines)</fld> <def>To remove the burned gases
from the cylinder after a working stroke; <as>as, this engine does not
<ex>scavenge</ex> well</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scavenger</ent>⟦br⟧
